getAllProteins

public void getAllProteins(java.util.Set<Protein> proteins)
This function returns all proteins that are used within this device. This means all expressed proteins, but also the dimers and tetramers they can form. It includes also the proteins that can bind any of the operators in this device. The set that is provided as argument will be filled.

Parameters:
proteins - Set of proteins.

getExpressedProteins

public void getExpressedProteins(java.util.Set<Protein> proteins)
This function returns all proteins that are expressed by this device. So only the monomeric proteins are returned. The set that is provided as argument will be filled.

Parameters:
proteins - Set of proteins.

getTFMonomers

public void getTFMonomers(java.util.Set<Protein> monomers)
This function returns all monomeric transcription factors that are part of a transcription factor that can bind to a operator from this device. It takes all the operators, takes all the transcription factors that bind to this operators and returns the monomers of these TFs. The set that is provided as argument will be filled.

Parameters:
monomers - Set of proteins.

getTFOligomers

public void getTFOligomers(java.util.Set<Protein> oligomers)
This function returns all oligomer forms (so all but the monomer) of the transcription factors that are part of this device. The set that is provided as argument will be filled.

Parameters:
oligomers - Set of proteins.

getPossibleSignals

public java.util.Set<EnvironmentalSignal> getPossibleSignals()
This function returns all environmental signals that bind one of the used transcription facters in this device. In other words, it returns all environmental signals that can be used as input to this device.

Returns:
Set of environmental signals.

getSignalTFs

public java.util.Set<TF> getSignalTFs(EnvironmentalSignal environmentalSignal)

Parameters:
environmentalSignal - An environmental signal.
Returns:
Set of transcription factors.

Set of transcription factors.

getIncompatibleSignals

public java.util.Set<EnvironmentalSignal> getIncompatibleSignals()
This function returns a set of environmental signals that are part of this device but do not bind any of the transcription factors. These environmental signals are thus useless, since they cannot have any influence on the device.

Returns:
Set of environmental signals.

getIncompatibleProteins

public java.util.Set<Protein> getIncompatibleProteins()

Returns:
Set of transcription factors.
